@node Transient menu
@section Transient menu

@findex agent-log-menu

The command @code{agent-log-menu} opens a transient menu that groups all @code{agent-log} commands into four columns: Open, Sync & AI, Navigate (shown only inside a @code{agent-log-mode} buffer), and Settings.  The keybinding is @samp{?} in @code{agent-log-mode}.  The menu is also available globally via its autoload, so you can bind it to a key of your choice outside of @code{agent-log-mode}.

The Open column includes @code{agent-log-resume-session} (bound to @samp{r}), which resumes the session displayed in the current buffer in the coding agent.  The Sync & AI column includes the @code{agent-log-search} command, bound to @samp{/}.

The Settings column displays the current value of each option (e.g., @code{collapsed}, @code{on}, @code{off}) highlighted with the @code{transient-value} face, matching the convention used by @samp{magit} and other transient-based menus.  In the Navigate column, @samp{G} refreshes the buffer; in the Settings column, @samp{g} toggles grouping by project.

